SIMPLE: sunstroke
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunstroke
<hw>Sun"stroke`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Any affection produced by the action of the sun on some part of the
body; especially, a sudden prostration of the physical powers, with
symptoms resembling those of apoplexy, occasioned by exposure to
excessive heat, and often terminating fatally; coup de soleil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sun-struck</ent>⟦br⟧
